indicating sardines are cooked through. If not, place Varoma back into position, secure Varoma lid and cook for a further <b>3-4 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Remove Varoma. Unwrap the eggs and cool them under running water."},{"content":"Remove simmering basket with aid of spatula and transfer cooked beans into a serving bowl, along with cherry tomatoes, spring onions, extra virgin olive oil, vinegar and salt. Peel cooked eggs, cut into wedges, add into the serving bowl and gently toss the salad. Open parcels and serve fish immediately with warm bean salad."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Replace fresh sardines with defrosted sardines or with other small oily fish of the same size and weight (e.g. mackerel).<br>- Replace sardines with <b>2 whole<b> sea bass, gutted (approx. <b>350-380 g each):<b> Use two <b>50 cm x<b> <b>30 cm<b> rectangles of oiled baking paper, make <b>1 parcel<b> for each seabass and proceed with <b>step 2.<b> Before serving, remove skin and bones and serve half a fish per portion.<br>- For a different flavour, add a bay leaf and thin lemon slices to each parcel, or sprinkle fish with ground sweet paprika and drizzle with extra virgin olive oil before serving."],"basicInfo":["easy","35m","1h","4 portions"]}